  "texts": [
    "The correlations involving τ -→ µ -µ + µ -, with the experimental upper bound B(τ -→ µ -µ + µ -) < 2.1×10 -8 [30] do not provide significant constraints for B s and B modes.",
    "Accounting for the measurement of the width of B s → µ + µ -, the largest value for B(τ -→ µ -µ + µ -) is about 1.2 × 10 -8.µ -→ e -γ puts more stringent limits.",
    "Figure 17 shows the correlation between B(B s → τ + µ -) and B(µ -→ e -γ) for M Z ′ = 1 TeV and 3 TeV.",
    "The dark points show the results without imposing constraints from LFC mode, the light points the results obtained imposing that the measured B(B s → µ + µ -) is recovered.",
    "The upper bound is displayed B(µ -→ e -γ) < 1.5 × 10 -13 (at 90% CL) recently established by the MEG II Collaboration [94] which has improved the previous limit B(µ -→ e -γ) < 4.2 × 10 -13 (at 90% CL) [97]."
